Captain Morgan.label: Captain Morgan
Captain Morgan.description: Captain Morgan is a brand of rum produced by alcohol conglomerate Diageo. It is named after the 17th-century Welsh privateer of the Caribbean, Sir Henry Morgan who died on 26 August 1688. Wikipedia

Guaraná Antarctica.label: Guaraná Antarctica
Guaraná Antarctica.description: Guaraná is a guaraná-flavoured soft drink, originating in Brazil and manufactured and distributed by Anheuser-Busch InBev. It was created in 1921 by Pedro Baptista de Andrade for Companhia Antarctica Paulista, now part of Anheuser-Busch InBev. Wikipedia

Dr Pepper.label: Dr Pepper Snapple Group
Dr Pepper.description:
Dr Pepper Snapple Group Inc. is an American soft drink company, based in Plano, Texas.
It was spun off from Britain's Cadbury Schweppes, on May 5, 2008, with trading in its shares starting on May 7, 2008. Wikipedia

Diet Coke.label: Diet Coke
Diet Coke.description: Diet Coke, called Coca-Cola Light in some countries, is a sugar-free soft drink produced and distributed by The Coca-Cola Company. Wikipedia

Mecca-Cola.label: Mecca-Cola
Mecca-Cola.description: Mecca-Cola is a cola-flavoured carbonated beverage. The flagship product of the Mecca Cola World Company, it is marketed as an alternative to U.S. brands such as Coca-Cola and Pepsi-Cola to "pro-Muslim" consumers. Wikipedia

Ginger ale.label: Ginger ale
Ginger ale.description: Ginger ale is a carbonated soft drink flavored with ginger in one of two ways. The golden style is closer to the ginger beer original, and is credited to the American doctor Thomas Cantrell. Wikipedia

Cointreau.label: Cointreau
Cointreau.description: Cointreau is a brand of triple sec produced in Saint-Barthélemy-d'Anjou, France. It is drunk as an apéritif and digestif, and is a component of several well-known cocktails. It was originally called "Curaçao Blanco Triple Sec". Wikipedia

Scotch whisky.label: Scotch whisky
Scotch whisky.description:
Scotch whisky, often simply called Scotch, is malt whisky or grain whisky made in Scotland. Scotch whisky must be made in a manner specified by law.
All Scotch whisky was originally made from malted barley. Wikipedia

Chartreuse (liqueur).label: Chartreuse
Chartreuse (liqueur).description: Chartreuse is a French liqueur made by the Carthusian Monks since 1737 according to the instructions set out in the secret manuscript given to them by François Annibal d'Estrées in 1605. Wikipedia

Hpnotiq.label: Hpnotiq
Hpnotiq.description: Hpnotiq liqueur is an alcoholic beverage, native to New York but bottled in France by Heaven Hill Distilleries, made from fruit juices, vodka and a cognac. It is 34 proof and is available in over 70 countries worldwide. Wikipedia

Jim Beam.label: Jim Beam
Jim Beam.description: Jim Beam is an American brand of bourbon whiskey produced in Clermont, Kentucky. It was one of the best selling brands of bourbon in the world in 2008. Wikipedia

Triple sec.label: Triple sec
Triple sec.description: Triple sec, originally Curaçao triple sec, is a variety of Curaçao liqueur, an orange-flavoured liqueur made from the dried peels of bitter and sweet orange. Wikipedia

Dewar's.label: Dewar's
Dewar's.description: Dewar's is a brand of blended Scotch whisky owned by Bacardi, which claims the brand's "White Label" to be the top-selling blended Scotch in the US. Wikipedia

Seagram's Seven Crown.label: Seagram's Seven Crown
Seagram's Seven Crown.description: Seagram's Seven Crown, otherwise known as Seagram's Seven, is a blended American whiskey produced by Diageo under the Seagram name. Seagram's beverage division was acquired by Diageo, Pernod, and The Coca-Cola Company in 2000. Wikipedia

Le Tourment Vert.label: Le Tourment Vert
Le Tourment Vert.description: Le Tourment Vert was an absinthe-like liqueur imported from the French Distillerie Vinet EGE, near the French commune of Cognac. The spirit was created in 2007. Wikipedia

Kahlúa.label: Kahlúa
Kahlúa.description: Kahlúa is a coffee-flavored rum-based liqueur from Mexico. The drink also contains sugar, corn syrup and vanilla bean. Wikipedia

Diet Pepsi.label: Diet Pepsi
Diet Pepsi.description: Diet Pepsi is a no-calorie carbonated cola soft drink produced by PepsiCo, introduced in 1964 as a variant of Pepsi-Cola with no sugar. Wikipedia

Boost (health food).label: Boost
Boost (health food).description: Boost is a chocolate-flavored health food drink manufactured by GlaxoSmithKline. It was launched in 1977 in India. Brand ambassador for Boost in 1986 was the cricketer Kapil Dev. Sachin Tendulkar became the brand ambassador with his debut in 1989. Wikipedia

Pepsi Max.label: PepsiCo
Pepsi Max.description: PepsiCo Inc. is an American multinational food and beverage corporation headquartered in Purchase, New York, United States, with interests in the manufacturing, marketing and distribution of grain-based snack foods, beverages, and other products. Wikipedia

SKYY vodka.label: SKYY vodka
SKYY vodka.description: SKYY vodka is produced by the Campari America division of Campari Group of Milan, Italy, formerly SKYY Spirits LLC. Wikipedia

Like Cola.label: Like Cola
Like Cola.description: Like Cola was an unsuccessful cola soft drink, introduced by the 7 Up company, that appeared on the American market in 1982. Its slogan was "Made From The Cola Nut." Like Cola was one of the first attempts at a cola without caffeine. Wikipedia

Qibla Cola.label: Qibla Cola
Qibla Cola.description: Qibla Cola a cola-flavored carbonated beverage is the flagship product of the Qibla Cola Company, based in Derby, England. Wikipedia

Crown Royal.label: Crown Royal
Crown Royal.description: Crown Royal is a blended Canadian whisky, 40% alcohol by volume, 80 proof. The brand is owned by Diageo, which purchased it when the Seagram portfolio was dissolved in the year 2000. It is the top-selling Canadian whisky in the United States. Wikipedia

Tascalate.label: Tascalate
Tascalate.description: Tascalate is a chocolate drink made from a mixture of chocolate, ground pine nuts, achiote, vanilla and sugar, very common in the Mexican state of Chiapas. Wikipedia

Solo (Australian soft drink).label: Solo
Solo (Australian soft drink).description:
In Australia, Solo is a carbonated lemon-flavoured soft drink manufactured by Schweppes Australia.
Solo was launched in Australia in 1973 as the ready to drink version of traditional 'pub squash'. Wikipedia

Woodford Reserve.label: Woodford Reserve
Woodford Reserve.description: Woodford Reserve is a brand of premium small batch Kentucky Straight Bourbon Whiskey produced by the Brown-Forman Corporation. It is distilled at the company's Woodford Reserve Distillery. The distillery is in Woodford County, in central Kentucky. Wikipedia
